Weight: 1~


//Armor
@40212 = ~Potion of Armor~
@40213 = ~The imbiber is granted a magical force that acts as scale mail armor (AC 6). It is cumulative with Dexterity bonuses to Armor Class and, in the case of Fighter/Mages, with the shield bonus.

STATISTICS:

Base AC: 6
Duration: 9 hours

Weight: 1~


//Friends
@40214 = ~Potion of Friends~
@40215 = ~This potion causes the imbiber to temporarily gain 6 points of Charisma. Those who view the imbiber tend to be very impressed with <PRO_HIMHER> and make an effort to be <PRO_HISHER> friends and help <PRO_HIMHER>, as appropriate to the situation.

STATISTICS:

Charisma: +6
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Protection From Petrification
@40216 = ~Potion of Protection From Petrification~
@40217 = ~This potion grants the imbiber immunity to all petrification attacks. This includes basilisk and medusa gaze, cursed scrolls of petrification, etc.

STATISTICS:

Special: Immune to petrification
Duration: 1 hour

Weight: 1~


//Protection From Evil
@40218 = ~Potion of Protection From Evil~
@40219 = ~This potion creates a magical barrier around the imbiber at a distance of one foot. The barrier moves with the imbiber and has two major effects: First, all attacks made by evil or evilly enchanted creatures against the protected creature receive a penalty of -2 to each attack roll. Second, summoned demons cannot target the protected creature.

STATISTICS:

Special: Evil creatures' attack rolls are -2; cannot be targeted by summoned demons
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Shield
@40220 = ~Oil of Shield~
@40221 = ~When poured, this oil dissolves into a translucent barrier in front of the applicant. It sets the applicant's Armor Class to 4 against all melee weapons, and 2 against missile weapons. It also grants the applicant immunity from the spell Magic Missile.

STATISTICS:

AC: 4 vs. melee; 2 vs. missile
Special: Immunity to Magic Missile spell
Duration: 1 hour

Weight: 1~


//Sleep
@40222 = ~Sleep Bomb~
@40223 = ~This bomb causes a comatose slumber to come upon one or more enemies around its impact. All creatures in the area of effect must make a Saving Throw vs. Spell or fall asleep. Attacks against sleeping opponents never miss, though they will wake upon taking damage.

STATISTICS:

Special: Sleep (Saving vs. Spell negates)
Range: 40 ft.
Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
Duration: 5 rounds

Weight: 1~


//Aid
@40224 = ~Potion of Aid~
@40225 = ~This potion raises the morale of the imbiber by +1. Furthermore, it raises their attack and damage rolls by +1, and 1d8 additional Hit Points for the duration.

STATISTICS:

Morale: +1 bonus
Attack rolls: +1 bonus
Damage rolls: +1 bonus
Hit Points: +1d8 temporary Hit Points
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Barkskin
@40226 = ~Oil of Barkskin~
@40227 = ~Upon application, this oil causes skin to become as tough as bark, increasing its base Armor Class to %base_AC%. In addition, Saving Throws (except magic) gain a +1 bonus.

STATISTICS:

Base AC: %base_AC%
Saving Throws: +1 bonus (except vs. Spell)
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Chant
@40228 = ~Potion of Chant~
@40229 = ~This potion grants the imbiber a +1 bonus to attack rolls, minimum damage rolls, and Saving Throws. Furthermore, damage dice for all effects outside a weapon's base damage is reduced by 1.

For example, a 6d6 fireball will do 6d5 damage, and a flaming long sword that deals 1d8+2 slashing plus 1d3 fire damage will deal 1d8+2 slashing plus 1d2 fire damage instead.

STATISTICS:

Attack rolls: +1 bonus
Damage rolls: +1 bonus
Saving Throws: +1 bonus
Special: dice rolled against imbiber (outside a weapon's base damage) are reduced by 1 size
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Find Traps
@40230 = ~Philter of Find Traps~
@40231 = ~This potion opens the mind of the imbiber; all traps —concealed normally or magically— of magical or mechanical nature become apparent to <PRO_HIMHER>. The imbiber must stop to concentrate 1/per round to observe surroundings.

STATISTICS:

Special: Find traps in immediate area
Duration: 3 turns (30 rounds)

Weight: 1~


//Resist Fire and Cold
@40232 = ~Potion of Resist Fire and Cold~
@40233 = ~This potion causes the imbiber's body to be toughened to withstand heat and cold; all damage sustained by fire or cold is reduced by 50%.

STATISTICS:

Fire resistance: +50% (mundane or magical)
Cold resistance: +50% (mundane or magical)
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Draw Upon Holy Might
@40234 = ~Draught of Draw Upon Holy Might~
@40235 = ~This potion grants %magnitude_points% of Strength, Constitution, and Dexterity to the imbiber

STATISTICS:

Strength:     +%magnitude% bonus
Dexterity:    +%magnitude% bonus
Constitution: +%magnitude% bonus
Duration: 1 turn (10 rounds)

Weight: 1~


//Writhing Fog
@40236 = ~Writhing Fog Bomb~
@40237 = ~This bomb conjures a cloud of writhing fog that chills and hinders anyone within its area. Creatures in the fog take 1d3 points of cold damage per round. In addition, there is a 20% chance that they must save vs. Death or be slowed for 1 round. Creatures immune to cold damage do not suffer any adverse effects from this spell.

STATISTICS:

Damage: 1d3 cold
Special: 20% chance slowed for 1 round (must save vs. Death negates)
Range: 40 ft.
Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
Duration: 1 turn (10 rounds)

Weight: 1~


//Blur
@40238 = ~Oil of Blur~
@40239 = ~When applied, this oil causes the outline of the applicant's form to become blurred, shifting, and wavering. This distortion causes all missile and melee attacks against the applicant to be made with a -3 penalty. The applicant also gains a +1 bonus to all of <PRO_HISHER> Saving Throws.

STATISTICS:

AC: +3 bonus
Saving Throws: +1 bonus
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Detect Invisibility
@40240 = ~Potion of Detect Invisibility~
@40241 = ~The imbiber is able to see clearly any objects or beings that are invisible, as well as any that are astral, ethereal, or out of phase. In addition, this potion enables the imbiber to detect hidden or concealed creatures (e.g., Thieves hiding in shadows, halflings in underbrush, and so on).

STATISTICS:

Special: Imbiber sees invisibility clearly
Duration: 4 turns (40 rounds)

Weight: 1~


//Knock
@40242 = ~Oil of Knock~
@40243 = ~When applied, this oil opens locked, held, or wizard-locked doors. It opens secret doors as well as locked boxes or chests. It does not raise barred gates or similar impediments.

STATISTICS:

Special: Unlocks any single lock
Duration: Instant

Weight: 1~


//Luck
@40244 = ~Potion of Luck~
@40245 = ~The imbiber gains extraordinary luck for the next 3 rounds, receiving a +1 bonus to <PRO_HISHER> Saving Throws, attack rolls, and minimum damage/healing rolls as well as +5% to all thieving skills. Furthermore, damage dice for all effects outside a weapon's base damage is reduced by 1.

For example, a 6d6 fireball will do 6d5 damage, and a flaming long sword that deals 1d8+2 slashing plus 1d3 fire damage will deal 1d8+2 slashing plus 1d2 fire damage instead.

STATISTICS:

Attack rolls: +1 bonus
Damage rolls: +1 bonus
Saving Throws: +1 bonus
Find Traps: +5%
Set Traps: +5%
Pick Pockets: +5%
Open Locks: +5%
Move Silently: +5%
Hide In Shadows: +5%
Detect Illusions: +5%
Special: dice rolled against imbiber (outside a weapon's base damage) are reduced by 1 size
Duration: 3 rounds

Weight: 1~


//Resist Fear
@40246 = ~Philter of Resist Fear~
@40247 = ~This potion instills courage in the imbiber, raising their morale to its highest. The imbiber's morale will gradually reset to normal as the duration runs out. If the imbiber is affected by magical fear, they will regain their composure.

STATISTICS:

Special: Immune to fear, panic
Duration: 3 rounds

Weight: 1~


//Mirror Image
@40248 = ~Oil of Mirror Image~
@40249 = ~When this oil is applied, the applicant shimmers and causes %magnitude% exact duplicates of <PRO_HIMHER>self to come into being around <PRO_HIMHER>. These images do exactly what the applicant does. Since the effect causes a blurring and slight distortion, it is impossible for opponents to be certain which are the illusions and which is real. When an image is struck by a melee or missile attack —magical or otherwise— it disappears, but any other existing images remain intact until they are struck. However, it is important to note that this will not protect the applicant against every attack, as it is possible for an enemy to choose the real caster amongst all the images.

STATISTICS:

Special: %magnitude% mirror images
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Stinking Cloud
@40250 = ~Bomb of Stinking Cloud~
@40251 = ~Upon impact, this bomb releases a billowing mass of nauseous vapors. Any creature caught within the cloud must roll a successful Saving Throw vs. Poison at +2 or be sent reeling and fall down for 1d2 rounds. Those who make successful Saving Throws can leave the cloud without suffering any ill effects, although those remaining in the cloud must continue to save each round. A Dispel Magic will remove the nausea on a particular character, but if they remain in the cloud, then they are still subject to its effects.

STATISTICS:

Special: fall prone for 1d2 rounds (save vs. Poison at +2 negates)
Range: 40 ft.
Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
Duration: 1 turn (10 rounds)

Weight: 1~


//Strength
@40252 = ~Potion of Strength~
@40253 = ~This potion sets the Strength of the imbiber to 18 and then adds a +50% bonus on top of this. The imbiber receives any strength bonuses appropriate.

For example, if a character has between 18/50 and 18/00 Strength, then <PRO_HISHER> Strength will just be set to 18/00. If a character has a Strength between 18/01 and 18/50, then <PRO_HISHER> Strength will become 18/50 + original percentage. If <PRO_HISHER> Strength is less than 18, then it will just become 18/50. However, this spell will actually lower a character's Strength if it is already 19 or more.

STATISTICS:

Strength: 18/+50
Duration: %num_turns% turns (%num_rounds% rounds)

Weight: 1~


//Web
@40254 = ~Web Bomb~
@40255 = ~This bomb impacts, releasing web-like substance covering a maximum area of about 15 ft. in radius. Creatures caught within webs, or simply touching them, become stuck among the gluey fibers. Anyone in the area must roll a Saving Throw vs. Spell with a -2 penalty. If the Saving Throw is successful, then the creature is free to move out of the area. A failed Saving Throw means the creature is stuck in the webs unable to move. Each round that a creature remains in the web, it must make a Saving Throw or be unable to move.

STATISTICS:

Special: Held (save vs. Spell at -2 negates)
Range: 40 ft.
Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
Duration: 1 turn (10 rounds)

Weight: 1~


//Vocalize
@40256 = ~Draught of Vocalize~
@40257 = ~The imbiber can cast spells with a verbal component without having to make any noise. Effectively, this spell cancels the effects of Silence and makes the recipient immune to it for the duration.

STATISTICS:

Special: Can cast spells without speech (bypassing silence, deafness, etc.)
Duration: 1 turn (10 rounds)

Weight: 1~


//Dispel Magic
@40258 = ~Vial of Dispel Magic~
@40259 = ~This bomb removes magical effects upon anyone within the area. This includes effects given from spells, potions and certain magical items such as wands. It does not, however, affect enchanted magical items or spell protections such as Spell Turning and Spell Deflection.

The base chance of successfully dispelling is 50%. For every level that this bomb exceeds the original caster level, the chance of success increases by 5%. For every level that this bomb is below the original caster level, the chance of success decreases by 10%. However, despite the difference in levels, there is always at least a 5% chance of success or failure. Thus, if the bomb is 10 levels higher than the magic it is trying to dispel, there is only a 5% chance of failure. Similarly if the bomb is 4 levels lower than the magic it is trying to dispel, there is only a 10% chance of success. Intuitively, this spell is almost useless if the target is 5 or more levels higher than the bomb.

Note: While this spell dispels the individual effects of Grease, Web, Stinking Cloud, and other such spells, it does not dispel the area of effect.

STATISTICS:

Special: Dispels magical effects
Range: 40 ft.
Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
Duration: Instant

Weight: 1~


//Protection From Fire
@40260 = ~Potion of Protection From Fire~
@40261 = ~This potion it confers complete invulnerability to normal fires (torches, bonfires, oil fires, and the like); and 50% to exposure to magical fire sources (fiery dragon breath, hell hound or pyrohydra breath, spells such as Burning Hands, Fireball, Fire Seeds, Fire Storm, Flame Strike, Meteor Swarm, and so on).

STATISTICS:

Fire resistance: +100%
Magical fire resistance: +50%
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Remove Curse
@40262 = ~Draught of Remove Curse~
@40263 = ~This potion is usually able to remove a curse on a person. Note that this potion does not remove the curse from a cursed shield, weapon, or suit of armor, although it typically enables the person afflicted with any such cursed item to get rid of it.

STATISTICS:

Special: Remove curse on imbiber
Duration: Instant

Weight: 1~


//Strength of One
@40264 = ~Phial of Strength of One~
@40265 = ~The imbiber is given a Strength score of 18/75. If the imbiber has a Strength score higher than 18/75 (either naturally, or through a magical item), then <PRO_HISHER> Strength is lowered to 18/75.

STATISTICS:

Strength: 18/75
Duration: 1 turn (10 rounds)

Weight: 1~


//Cure Medium Wounds
@40266 = ~Potion of Medium Healing~
@40267 = ~When wholly consumed, this potion restores 14 Hit Points to the imbiber. The effect is instantaneous and the potion is destroyed in the process.

STATISTICS:

Special: Restores 14 Hit Points.
Duration: Instant

Weight: 1~


//Cure Disease
@40268 = ~Potion of Cure Disease~
@40269 = ~This potion will cure almost any disease. The cure is permanent, but does not grant the imbiber of the spell immunity from further afflictions. Blindness, deafness, and feeblemind are also cured with this spell. Some magically created diseases may not be curable by this spell.

STATISTICS:

Special: Removes disease, blindness, deafness, and feeblemindedness.
Duration: Instant

Weight: 1~


//Zone of Sweet Air
@40270 = ~Bottled Sweet Air~
@40271 = ~When unstoppered, this potion repels all noxious elements from poisonous vapors (including magically created vapors such as Cloudkill). This spell will dismiss all clouds in the entire area that the activator is currently in.

STATISTICS:

Special: Removes cloud vapor effects.
Duration: Instant

Weight: 1~


//Fireball
@40272 = ~Fire Bomb~
@40273 = ~This bomb blossoms into a fireball upon impact, dealing %magnitude%d6 damage to those in the blast radius. Creatures who roll successful Saving Throws manage to dodge, fall flat, or roll aside the blast, each receiving only half damage.

STATISTICS:

Damage: %magnitide%d6 (Save vs. Spell for half)
Range: 40 ft.
Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
Duration: Instant

Weight: 1~


//Non-Detection
@40274 = ~Potion of Non-Detection~
@40275 = ~This potion makes the imbiber undetectable by divination spells such as Clairaudience, Clairvoyance, Locate Object, ESP, and detect spells including Invisibility Purge. It also prevents location by such magical items as crystal balls and ESP medallions. It does not affect the Know Alignment spell.

STATISTICS:

Special: Prevents detection via magical divination.
Duration: 4 hours

Weight: 1~


//Protection From Normal Missiles
@40276 = ~Oil of Protection From Normal Missiles~
@40277 = ~This oil provides total invulnerability to non-magical hurled and launched missiles such as arrows, bolts, bullets, darts, throwing axes, and throwing daggers. Note, however, that this potion does not convey any protection from such magical attacks as Fireball, Lightning Bolt, or Magic Missile, nor does it protect against magical missiles such as arrows +1.

STATISTICS:

Special: Immune to non-magical missile damage
Duration: 4 hours

Weight: 1~


//Wraithform
@40278 = ~Potion of Wraithform~
@40279 = ~The imbiber and all of <PRO_HISHER> gear become insubstantial, subject only to magical or special attacks, including those by weapons of +1 or better enchantment, or by creatures otherwise able to affect those struck only by magical weapons. The imbiber also gains 25% resistance to magic damage. While in wraithform, the imbiber cannot cast either arcane or divine spells.

STATISTICS:

Magic Resistance: +25%
Special: Immune to non-magical damage
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Ghost Armor
@40280 = ~Oil of Ghost Armor~
@40281 = ~This oil dissolves into a magical field of force that serves as if it were field plate armor (AC 2). It is cumulative with Dexterity bonuses to Armor Class and, in the case of Fighter/Mages, with the shield's bonus. The effect does not hinder movement, adds no weight or encumbrance, nor does it prevent spellcasting. It lasts until successfully dispelled or until the duration expires.

STATISTICS:

Base AC: 2
Duration: 1 hours

Weight: 1~


//Protection From Cold
@40282 = ~Potion of Protection From Cold~
@40283 = ~This potion confers complete invulnerability to normal cold attacks and partial protection from exposure to magical cold such as an icy dragon's breath, spells such as Cone of Cold, etc., absorbing 50% of all the damage dealt by such magical sources.

STATISTICS:

Cold resistance: +100%
Magical cold resistance: +50%
Duration: %num_turns turns (%num_rounds% rounds)

Weight: 1~


//Cure Serious Wounds
@40284 = ~Potion of Modest Healing~
@40285 = ~When wholly consumed, this potion restores 17 Hit Points to the imbiber. The effect is instantaneous and the potion is destroyed in the process.

STATISTICS:

Special: Restores 17 Hit Points.
Duration: Instant

Weight: 1~


//Free Action
@40286 = ~Philter of Free Action~
@40287 = ~This potion caused to imbiber to become immune to anything that affects <PRO_HISHER> movement. This includes the effects of Web, Hold Person, Grease, and Entangle.

STATISTICS:

Special: Immune to holding effects or changes to movement rate
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Death Ward
@40288 = ~Draught of Death Ward~
@40289 = ~This potion protects the imbiber from all forms of death magic for the duration of the spell. This includes, but is not limited to: Disintegrate; Power Word, Kill; Death Spell; and Finger of Death.

STATISTICS:

Special: Immune to death magic
Duration: %num_turns turns (%num_rounds% rounds)

Weight: 1~


//Holy Power
@40290 = ~Potion of Holy Power~
@40291 = ~This potion gives the imbiber the strength and skill of a Fighter of level %magnitude%. The imbiber's Strength score is set to 18/00 —even if it is normally higher— <PRO_HISHER> THAC0 becomes that of a Fighter and <PRO_HESHE> gains %magnitude% temporary Hit Points.

This will last for the duration of the spell or until dispelled.

STATISTICS:

Strength: 18/00
THAC0: +%magnitude2% bonus
HP: +%magnitude% temporary hit points
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Negative Plane Protection
@40292 = ~Philter of Negative Plane Protection~
@40293 = ~This potion provies partial protection from undead monsters with Negative Energy Plane connections (such as vampires), and certain weapons and spells that drain energy levels.

A protected creature struck by a negative energy attack is protected against any form of level draining for the duration of the potion's effect. The protected creature suffers only normal Hit Point damage from the attack and does not suffer any drain of experience.

STATISTICS:

Special: Protected from level drain
Duration: 8 hours

Weight: 1~


//Cloak of Fear
@40294 = ~Phial of Fear~
@40295 = ~This potion cloaks the imbiber with an aura of fear in a 5-ft. radius. All creatures that enter the cloak's area of effect must make a Save vs. Spell or flee in panic for 1 round. The aura does not affect undead creatures.

STATISTICS:

Special: nearby creatures flee in panic (save vs. Spell negates)
Duration: 1 turn (10 rounds)

Weight: 1~


//Lesser Restoration
@40296 = ~Potion of Lesser Restoration~
@40297 = ~This potion causes the life energy level of the imbiber to raise. This reverses any previous level drain of the creature by a force or monster.

The effects of the potion are very draining, as it will cause a day's worth of fatigue almost instantaneously.

STATISTICS:

Special: Removes level drain; causes fatigue
Duration: Instant

Weight: 1~


//Spirit Fire
@40298 = ~Bomb of Spirit Fire~
@40299 = ~This bomb causes spirit world energies to form; it explodes into a burst of ghostly, azure flames, which deliver %magnitude%d4 points of magic damage. There is also a 33% chance that every enemy within the area of effect will be afflicted by the Doom spell (-2 penalty to Saving Throws and attack rolls for 1 turn). A successful Save vs. Spell halves the damage and negates the Doom effect. Spirits, fey creatures, elementals, and spectral undead take double damage.

STATISTICS:

Damage: %magnitide%d4 magic (Save vs. Spell for half); 33% chance of Doom (-2 attack roll and saving throw penalty for 1 turn)
Range: 40 ft.
Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
Duration: Instant

Weight: 1~


//Fireshield (Blue)
@40300 = ~Oil of Blue Fireshield~
@40301 = ~This oil, when poured in a circle, ignites into shield of icy flame which protects the user from cold damage. This shield not only grants the user 50% Cold Resistance, but also protects the applicant from attacks made within a 5-ft. radius around the caster. An opponent that hits the caster with any weapons or spells within this radius suffers 1d8+2 cold damage.

STATISTICS:

Damage: 1d8+2 cold
Cold Resistance: +50% (mundane or magical)
Area of Effect: 5-ft. radius
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Improved Invisibility
@40302 = ~Potion of Improved Invisibility~
@40303 = ~This potion renders the imbiber invisible. The imbiber is able to attack by missile discharge, melee combat, or spellcasting while remaining unseen. However, telltale traces —a shimmering— allow an observant opponent to attack the invisible spell imbiber. These traces are only noticeable when specifically looked for (after the invisible character has made <PRO_HISHER> presence known). Attacks against the invisible character suffer a -4 penalty to attack rolls, and the invisible character's Saving Throws are made with a +4 bonus.

Note: After making an attack, the imbiber is no longer completely invisible and can be targeted by opponents.

STATISTICS:

Special: Invisible, may attack and remain partially hidden

Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Minor Globe of Invulnerability
@40304 = ~Oil of Minor Invulnerability Globe~
@40305 = ~When applied, this oil creates a faintly shimmering magical sphere around the applicant that prevents any 1st-, 2nd-, or 3rd-level spell effects from penetrating (i.e., the area of effect of any such spells does not include the area of the Minor Globe of Invulnerability). This includes innate abilities and effects from devices. However, any type of spell can be cast out of the magical sphere, and these pass from the caster of the globe to their subject without affecting the globe. Spells of 4th level or higher are not affected by the globe.

STATISTICS:

Special: Immune to opponent's 1st-, 2nd-, and 3rd-level spells
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Stoneskin
@40306 = ~Potion of Stoneskin~
@40307 = ~Upon drinking this potion, an outer skin of stone will move up from the ground, completely covering the imbiber. The effect of this is to protect the imbiber from physical attacks such as melee weapons and projectiles.  The skins will remain on the imbiber until <PRO_HESHE> is affected by a Dispel Magic, all of the skins are removed due to physical attacks, or the spell duration expires.

It is important to note that this will not protect the wizard from any magical attacks, such as Fireball.

STATISTICS:

Special: %magnitude% stone skins providing immunity to non-magical damage
Duration: 12 hours

Weight: 1~


//Greater Malison
@40308 = ~Bomb of Greater Malison~
@40309 = ~This bomb adversely affects all the Saving Throws of hostile creatures within the area of effect from the impact. Opponents under the influence of this spell make all Saving Throws at a penalty of -4.

STATISTICS:

Saving Throws: -4 penalty
Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Otiluke's Resilient Sphere
@40310 = ~Flask of Otiluke's Resilient Sphere~
@40311 = ~A globe of shimmering force encloses the target creature if it fails to Save vs. Spell. The resilient sphere will contain its subject for the duration of the spell. The sphere is completely immune to all damage; in fact, the only method of removing the sphere is a successful Dispel Magic.

Hence, the creature caught inside the globe is completely safe from all attacks, but at the same time completely unable to affect the outside world.

STATISTICS:

Special: Immune to damage; cannot attack (save vs. Spell negates)
Area of Effect: 1 Creature
Duration: 1 turn (10 rounds)

Weight: 1~


//Spirit Armor
@40312 = ~Oil of Spirit Armor~
@40313 = ~This oil creates a corporeal barrier around the applicant's body for the duration of the effect. This oil, however, actually taps in to the target's life force in order to create the barrier. The armor itself is weightless and does not hinder movement or spellcasting at all.

The spirit armor does not work cumulatively with any other armor; however, Dexterity bonuses still apply as well as magic rings and shields. While in effect, the Armor Class of the applicant will be set to 1, as if <PRO_HESHE> were wearing full plate. Also, due to the magical nature of the spell, <PRO_HESHE> will also receive a +3 bonus to Save vs. Spell.

There is a danger, however, as when the spell runs out, the external portion of the spirit is temporarily lost, inflicting 2d4 points of damage upon the applicant unless the creature makes a Saving Throw vs. Spell.

STATISTICS:

Base AC: 1
Saveing Throws: +3 bonus to save vs. Spell
Special: Imbiber takes 2d4 damage after duration
Duration: 2 hours

Weight: 1~


//Enchanted Weapon
@40314 = ~Oil of Enchanted Weapon~
@40315 = ~When this oil is applied, it enchants any weapons that the applicant currently wields; those weapons are treated as having a +3 enchantment for the purposes of determining what they can hit.

STATISTICS:

Special: weapons hit as if +3 enchanted weapons
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//Fireshield (Red)
@40316 = ~Oil of Red Fireshield~
@40317 = ~This oil, when poured in a circle, ignites into shield of brilliant flame which protects the user from fire damage. This shield not only grants the user 50% Fire Resistance, but also protects the applicant from attacks made within a 5-ft. radius around the caster. An opponent that hits the caster with any weapons or spells within this radius suffers 1d8+2 fire damage.

STATISTICS:

Damage: 1d8+2 fire
Fire Resistance: +50% (mundane or magical)
Area of Effect: 5-ft. radius
Duration: %num_rounds% rounds

Weight: 1~


//True Sight
@40318 = ~Philter of True Sight~
@40319 = ~This potion allows the imbiber perfect sight each round within 120 ft.; all hostile Illusion/Phantasm spells in the area of effect will be dispelled.

The spells that are affected by this are Reflected Image, Invisibility, Mirror Image, Non-Detection, Improved Invisibility, Shadow Door, Mislead, Project Image, and Simulacrum. The area of effect is roughly a 120-ft. radius around the imbiber. The target's Magic Resistance, if any, does not come into effect with this spell. This spell only affects enemies; thus, it is unable to dispel the invisibility from a party member.

STATISTICS:

Special: Dispels hostile illusions 1/round
Area of Effect: 120-ft. radius
Duration: 1 turn (10 rounds)

Weight: 1~


//Champion's Strength
@40320 = ~Potion of Champion's Strength~
@40321 = ~The imbiber's Strength is set to 25 for the duration of the effect, and gains %magnitude% bonus to THAC0. There is a drawback: the imbiber loses the ability to cast any spells during this time.

